-- 2. AlphaRet Exfoliating Peel Pads
UPDATE products SET
  image_url = '/images/products/skinbetter/peel-pads.jpg',
  price = 95.00,
  size = '30 pads',
  description = 'AlphaRet® Exfoliating Peel Pads are a convenient at-home chemical peel by skinbetter science that deliver professional-grade exfoliation in a single pre-soaked pad. Each pad combines glycolic acid, lactic acid, and salicylic acid with skinbetter''s patented AlphaRet technology—providing multi-acid resurfacing with built-in retinoid benefits. The result is immediate brightening and texture refinement that typically requires an in-office peel. Available at RELUXE Med Spa in Westfield and Carmel, Indiana.

These peel pads are a game-changer for patients who want visible smoothing between clinic visits. Use them 1-2 times per week for an instant glow before events, or as a regular texture-refining step in your evening routine. The triple-acid formula exfoliates at the surface (glycolic), mid-level (lactic), and within pores (salicylic), while AlphaRet stimulates cell turnover underneath. Our Hamilton County patients love keeping a jar at home for pre-event radiance and weekly maintenance between microneedling or laser sessions at RELUXE.',
  faq = '[{"q":"How often should I use the peel pads?","a":"Start with once per week in the evening. If your skin tolerates it well after 2-3 weeks, you can increase to twice weekly. Do not use on the same night as AlphaRet Overnight Cream."},{"q":"Can I use these with my AlphaRet Overnight Cream?","a":"Yes, but on alternate nights. Use peel pads 1-2 times per week and AlphaRet Overnight Cream on the other nights. Your RELUXE provider in Westfield or Carmel can help build the right schedule for your skin."},{"q":"Are these good before events or special occasions?","a":"Absolutely—that''s one of their best uses. Use a pad the night before a wedding, date night, or photo event for instant brightening and smoothing. Our Carmel and Westfield patients call them their event-prep secret."},{"q":"Where can I buy AlphaRet Peel Pads near me in Indiana?","a":"AlphaRet Exfoliating Peel Pads are available through our authorized skinbetter science store and at both RELUXE Med Spa locations in Westfield and Carmel, Indiana."}]'::JSONB,
  staff_picks = '{"westfield":"Our Westfield team''s event-prep secret—one pad the night before delivers an instant glow that patients across Hamilton County swear by.","carmel":"The easiest active in any routine. Carmel patients love these for weekly texture maintenance between microneedling and laser sessions at RELUXE."}'::JSONB,
  related_services = ARRAY['microneedling', 'chemical-peels']
WHERE slug = 'alpharet-peel-pads';

-- 3. Alto Advanced Defense and Repair Serum
UPDATE products SET
  image_url = '/images/products/skinbetter/alto.jpg',
  price = 175.00,
  size = '30ml / 1 fl oz',
  description = 'Alto Advanced Defense and Repair Serum is a broad-spectrum antioxidant treatment by skinbetter science that provides comprehensive environmental protection for your skin every morning. Combining 19 powerful antioxidants including vitamin C, vitamin E, and the rare Lipochroman compound, Alto defends against UV-induced free radical damage, visible light, infrared radiation, and pollution. This is the AM counterpart to the AlphaRet PM protocol—together they form one of the most effective anti-aging programs in professional skincare. Available at RELUXE Med Spa in Westfield and Carmel, Indiana.

What makes Alto Advanced unique is its multi-pathway approach to antioxidant protection. Rather than relying on a single ingredient, the formula combines fat-soluble and water-soluble antioxidants that work in different cellular compartments, providing overlapping defense at every level. Lipochroman is particularly notable—it protects against both reactive oxygen and nitrogen species, a capability few other antioxidants offer. For patients in Hamilton County dealing with Indiana''s variable climate—intense summer UV, winter wind, and seasonal shifts—Alto provides the daily environmental shield your skin needs year-round.',
  faq = '[{"q":"When should I apply Alto Advanced?","a":"Every morning after cleansing, before your SPF. Apply 2-3 pumps to face, neck, and chest. Allow 30 seconds to absorb, then apply your Colorescience Face Shield or mineral sunscreen over it."},{"q":"Can I use Alto with other vitamin C serums?","a":"Alto is designed as a complete antioxidant system—you don''t need additional vitamin C when using it. If you also use SkinCeuticals CE Ferulic, alternate days or use one AM and consult your RELUXE provider for the ideal protocol."},{"q":"What makes Alto different from basic vitamin C serums?","a":"Alto contains 19 antioxidants including Lipochroman, which protects against reactive nitrogen species that standard vitamin C cannot address. It provides broader defense against UV, visible light, infrared, and pollution—not just free radicals from UV alone."},{"q":"Where can I buy Alto Advanced near me in Indiana?","a":"Alto Advanced Defense and Repair Serum is available through our authorized skinbetter science store and at both RELUXE Med Spa locations—Westfield and Carmel, Indiana."}]'::JSONB,
  staff_picks = '{"westfield":"Your morning defense layer. Our Westfield team pairs Alto AM with AlphaRet PM for the gold-standard anti-aging protocol—patients across Hamilton County see dramatic improvement in firmness and glow.","carmel":"The Carmel team''s most-recommended morning serum. Layers under Colorescience SPF for complete environmental defense whether you''re walking the Monon Trail or at your desk."}'::JSONB,
  related_services = ARRAY['microneedling', 'chemical-peels', 'laser-resurfacing']
WHERE slug = 'alto-advanced';

-- 4. InterFuse Treatment Cream EYE
UPDATE products SET
  image_url = '/images/products/skinbetter/interfuse-eye.jpg',
  price = 120.00,
  size = '15ml / 0.5 fl oz',
  description = 'InterFuse® Treatment Cream EYE is a peptide-rich eye treatment by skinbetter science that targets every major sign of aging around the delicate peri-orbital area—fine lines, crepiness, puffiness, and dark circles. The proprietary InterFuse delivery system uses encapsulated technology to enhance penetration of active peptides and retinol into skin that''s notoriously difficult to treat. This is the eye treatment our RELUXE injectors recommend between Botox and filler appointments. Available at RELUXE Med Spa in Westfield and Carmel, Indiana.

The eye area ages faster than any other zone on the face because the skin is up to 10x thinner, produces less oil, and endures constant movement from blinking and expressions. InterFuse EYE was designed specifically for these challenges. The peptide complex stimulates collagen in this thin tissue while caffeine addresses puffiness and dark circles. Niacinamide strengthens the barrier, and microencapsulated retinol works beneath the surface to smooth texture. For our Hamilton County patients using neuromodulators, this product extends the visible benefits of Botox between appointments—maintaining smoothness and brightness in the crow''s feet and under-eye area daily.',
  faq = '[{"q":"Can I use InterFuse EYE with Botox?","a":"Yes—it''s one of the best daily complements to neuromodulator treatments. InterFuse EYE maintains smoothness and brightness between Botox appointments. Our RELUXE injectors in Westfield and Carmel recommend it to all their eye-area patients."},{"q":"Is InterFuse EYE safe for sensitive eyes?","a":"The formula is ophthalmologist tested and specifically designed for the delicate peri-orbital area. Apply along the orbital bone with your ring finger using gentle patting motions—never drag or pull."},{"q":"How does the InterFuse delivery system work?","a":"InterFuse uses encapsulated technology to deliver active peptides and retinol deeper into the thin eye-area skin than standard formulas can achieve. The microencapsulation also reduces irritation by releasing ingredients gradually."},{"q":"Where can I get professional eye treatments near me in Hamilton County?","a":"RELUXE Med Spa offers comprehensive eye-area treatments at both our Westfield and Carmel locations—including Botox, filler, and medical-grade skincare like InterFuse EYE. Book a consultation to build your personalized eye protocol."}]'::JSONB,
  staff_picks = '{"westfield":"Our Westfield injectors'' favorite eye product. Extends the benefits of Botox between appointments—patients who add InterFuse EYE consistently look fresher longer.","carmel":"The Carmel team''s go-to for anyone concerned about the eye area. Peptides + retinol + caffeine in one elegant formula that plays perfectly with injectable treatments at RELUXE."}'::JSONB,
  related_services = ARRAY['botox', 'filler', 'microneedling']
WHERE slug = 'interfuse-eye';

-- 5. Trio Rebalancing Moisture Treatment
UPDATE products SET
  image_url = '/images/products/skinbetter/trio.jpg',
  price = 125.00,
  size = '50ml / 1.7 fl oz',
  description = 'Trio Rebalancing Moisture Treatment is a lightweight yet effective barrier-support moisturizer by skinbetter science that combines ceramides, essential fatty acids, and cholesterol in a biomimetic ratio that mirrors the skin''s natural lipid composition. Unlike heavy creams that can clog pores or interfere with active ingredients, Trio provides the hydration and barrier protection your skin needs without compromising the performance of retinoids, acids, or vitamin C underneath. Available at RELUXE Med Spa in Westfield and Carmel, Indiana.

Trio is the glue that holds an active skincare routine together. When patients start potent ingredients like AlphaRet or chemical exfoliants, the skin barrier needs support—and Trio provides exactly that without heaviness or shine. It''s one of the few moisturizers that works beautifully across all skin types, from dry winter skin in Indiana to oily summer skin during Hamilton County''s humid months. Our RELUXE clinicians use it as the buffer during retinoid introduction: layered over AlphaRet on the first few nights, it reduces irritation without diminishing the retinoid''s effectiveness.',
  faq = '[{"q":"Is Trio heavy or greasy?","a":"No—despite being a barrier-repair moisturizer, Trio has a lightweight, fast-absorbing texture. It works for all skin types including oily and acne-prone skin without causing congestion or shine."},{"q":"Can I use Trio with AlphaRet Overnight Cream?","a":"Absolutely—that''s one of its best uses. Layer Trio over AlphaRet when you''re first starting or when your skin feels sensitive. It buffers irritation without reducing the retinoid''s effectiveness."},{"q":"Do I need this if my skin isn''t dry?","a":"Yes. Trio isn''t just for dry skin—it''s barrier support. Even oily and combination skin types need barrier protection, especially when using active ingredients like retinoids, acids, or vitamin C. It helps your actives work better."},{"q":"Where can I buy skinbetter science near me in Westfield or Carmel?","a":"Trio Rebalancing Moisture Treatment and the full skinbetter science line are available at both RELUXE Med Spa locations in Westfield and Carmel, Indiana. Shop online or visit us for a complimentary skin consultation."}]'::JSONB,
  staff_picks = '{"westfield":"The unsung hero of every skincare routine at our Westfield clinic. Trio makes retinoid introduction comfortable and keeps barrier function strong through Indiana''s harsh seasonal swings.","carmel":"Our Carmel team recommends Trio to every patient starting AlphaRet—it''s the moisturizer that makes active ingredients tolerable and effective. Lightweight enough for Hamilton County summers, supportive enough for winter."}'::JSONB,
  related_services = ARRAY['microneedling', 'chemical-peels', 'laser-resurfacing']
