-- 2. Phloretin CF
UPDATE products SET
  image_url = '/images/products/skinceuticals/phloretin.jpg',
  price = 182.00,
  size = '30ml / 1 fl oz',
  description = 'Phloretin CF® is a brightening antioxidant serum by SkinCeuticals formulated specifically for combination and oily skin types. The patented formula combines 2% phloretin, 10% L-ascorbic acid, and 0.5% ferulic acid to provide environmental protection while simultaneously addressing discoloration, uneven tone, and fine lines. Where CE Ferulic is the gold standard for dry-to-normal skin, Phloretin CF is the gold standard for combination and oily skin—delivering comparable antioxidant power with a lighter, oil-friendly texture. Available exclusively at RELUXE Med Spa in Westfield and Carmel, Indiana.

Phloretin is a naturally occurring antioxidant found in apple seeds that provides unique skin-brightening benefits beyond standard vitamin C. It inhibits melanin transport to the skin surface, making it particularly effective for patients dealing with post-inflammatory hyperpigmentation, sun spots, and melasma alongside oily or combination skin. The lightweight fluid texture absorbs quickly without adding shine or congestion—critical for patients who struggle with midday oiliness in Indiana''s humid summers. Our RELUXE clinicians recommend Phloretin CF for any combination-skin patient who wants the antioxidant power of CE Ferulic without the richer texture.',
  faq = '[{"q":"Should I use CE Ferulic or Phloretin CF?","a":"If your skin is dry or normal, CE Ferulic is ideal. If your skin is combination or oily, Phloretin CF is your match. Both provide powerful antioxidant protection—the difference is texture and secondary benefits. Your RELUXE provider in Westfield or Carmel can help you choose during a complimentary consultation."},{"q":"Does Phloretin CF help with dark spots?","a":"Yes—phloretin actively inhibits melanin transport, making it one of the most effective antioxidant serums for discoloration and uneven tone in oily/combination skin types."},{"q":"Can I use Phloretin CF with other SkinCeuticals products?","a":"Absolutely. Apply Phloretin CF first in the morning, then layer your SPF. In the evening, pair with Discoloration Defense for enhanced brightening or Silymarin CF if you need additional oil control."},{"q":"Where can I buy SkinCeuticals in Westfield or Carmel?","a":"SkinCeuticals is available exclusively at authorized providers. Visit RELUXE Med Spa at our Westfield or Carmel location for the full SkinCeuticals line and a complimentary skin consultation."}]'::JSONB,
  staff_picks = '{"westfield":"Our Westfield team''s vitamin C pick for combination skin patients. Brightens and protects without adding shine—perfect for Hamilton County patients who get oily in summer humidity.","carmel":"Phloretin CF is the Carmel team''s answer for patients who want CE Ferulic''s power but have oily or combination skin. Lighter texture, same-tier protection, plus additional brightening benefits for pigment-prone skin."}'::JSONB,
  related_services = ARRAY['chemical-peels', 'ipl-photofacial', 'microneedling']
WHERE slug = 'phloretin-cf';

-- 3. Silymarin CF
UPDATE products SET
  image_url = '/images/products/skinceuticals/silymarin.jpg',
  price = 172.00,
  size = '30ml / 1 fl oz',
  description = 'Silymarin CF is an antioxidant serum by SkinCeuticals specifically formulated for oily and blemish-prone skin. Combining 0.5% silymarin (milk thistle extract), 15% L-ascorbic acid, 0.5% ferulic acid, and 0.5% salicylic acid, it provides the environmental protection of a vitamin C serum while simultaneously reducing oiliness, refining pores, and preventing acne marks from becoming lasting hyperpigmentation. This is the vitamin C serum that finally works for breakout-prone skin. Available exclusively at RELUXE Med Spa in Westfield and Carmel, Indiana.

For years, oily and acne-prone patients were stuck choosing between antioxidant protection and clear skin—most vitamin C serums either triggered breakouts or felt too heavy. Silymarin CF solved that problem. The oil-free formula absorbs instantly, the salicylic acid keeps pores clear, and silymarin (a potent antioxidant from milk thistle) specifically supports oil-prone skin by improving texture and preventing oxidative damage from sebum. For our Hamilton County patients dealing with adult acne or post-acne marks, Silymarin CF provides the environmental defense their skin needs without any of the drawbacks. It''s also the preferred vitamin C for patients on prescription acne medications—compatible with tretinoin, adapalene, and other topical acne treatments.',
  faq = '[{"q":"Will Silymarin CF break me out?","a":"No—Silymarin CF was specifically formulated for acne-prone skin. The oil-free formula includes salicylic acid to keep pores clear, and clinical studies showed improvement in skin oiliness and texture. It''s the first vitamin C serum designed to work with breakout-prone skin, not against it."},{"q":"Can I use Silymarin CF with my acne medications?","a":"Yes. Silymarin CF is compatible with topical retinoids (tretinoin, adapalene), benzoyl peroxide, and other acne treatments. Apply Silymarin CF in the morning and use acne medications in the evening as directed by your RELUXE provider."},{"q":"How is Silymarin CF different from CE Ferulic?","a":"Both provide powerful antioxidant protection, but Silymarin CF is specifically formulated for oily and blemish-prone skin. It includes salicylic acid for pore refinement and silymarin for oil control—benefits CE Ferulic doesn''t offer. CE Ferulic is better for dry/normal skin; Silymarin CF is the choice for oily/acne-prone."},{"q":"Where can I get acne treatment near me in Indiana?","a":"RELUXE Med Spa offers comprehensive acne treatment at both our Westfield and Carmel locations. Silymarin CF is part of our recommended acne skincare protocol, paired with in-clinic treatments like chemical peels and laser therapy."}]'::JSONB,
  staff_picks = '{"westfield":"Vitamin C for acne-prone skin that actually works. Our Westfield team recommends Silymarin CF to every breakout-prone patient—it protects, brightens, and clears pores without triggering congestion.","carmel":"The Carmel team''s go-to for adult acne patients who also want anti-aging benefits. Silymarin CF provides vitamin C protection without shine, oiliness, or breakouts—game-changer for Hamilton County patients managing acne and aging simultaneously."}'::JSONB,
  related_services = ARRAY['chemical-peels', 'acne-treatment', 'microneedling']
WHERE slug = 'silymarin-cf';

-- 4. Discoloration Defense
UPDATE products SET
  image_url = '/images/products/skinceuticals/discoloration.jpg',
  price = 104.00,
  size = '30ml / 1 fl oz',
  description = 'Discoloration Defense is a multi-pathway pigment-correcting serum by SkinCeuticals that targets stubborn dark spots, post-inflammatory hyperpigmentation, and melasma at multiple stages of melanin production. The formula combines 3% tranexamic acid, 1% kojic acid, 5% niacinamide, and 5% HEPES to inhibit melanin synthesis, reduce melanin transfer, and accelerate cell turnover simultaneously—a comprehensive approach that delivers visible improvement in discoloration where single-ingredient products fail. Available exclusively at RELUXE Med Spa in Westfield and Carmel, Indiana.

Pigment disorders are among the most frustrating skin concerns because they''re triggered by so many factors—UV exposure, hormones, inflammation, and heat. Indiana''s strong summer sun and seasonal shifts make pigmentation especially persistent for Hamilton County residents. Discoloration Defense was formulated to address this complexity with a four-ingredient approach that works at every step of the pigmentation pathway. Tranexamic acid reduces UV-triggered melanin signals. Kojic acid inhibits the tyrosinase enzyme that produces melanin. Niacinamide blocks melanin transfer to the skin surface. HEPES accelerates cell turnover to shed pigmented cells faster. Together, they produce measurable lightening of dark spots within 6-12 weeks—and the improvement compounds with continued use. Our RELUXE providers pair Discoloration Defense with daily mineral SPF, periodic IPL or chemical peels, and Colorescience Even Up for the most complete pigment management protocol available.',
  faq = '[{"q":"How fast will I see results from Discoloration Defense?","a":"Most patients notice visible improvement in overall radiance within 2 weeks. Measurable reduction in stubborn dark spots and hyperpigmentation typically appears at the 6-12 week mark with consistent twice-daily use."},{"q":"Can I use this for melasma treatment?","a":"Yes—Discoloration Defense is one of the cornerstone products in our melasma protocol at RELUXE Med Spa. The tranexamic acid specifically targets hormonal and UV-triggered pigmentation. Pair it with mineral SPF daily and periodic in-clinic treatments for best results."},{"q":"Is it safe for all skin tones?","a":"Yes. Discoloration Defense is safe and effective across all Fitzpatrick skin types. The formula avoids hydroquinone, making it suitable for long-term use without risk of paradoxical darkening that some other lightening agents can cause."},{"q":"Where can I get dark spot treatment near me in Carmel or Westfield?","a":"RELUXE Med Spa offers comprehensive pigment correction at both Hamilton County locations. Discoloration Defense is part of our at-home pigment protocol, paired with in-clinic IPL, chemical peels, and Colorescience Even Up SPF for complete melasma and hyperpigmentation management."}]'::JSONB,
  staff_picks = '{"westfield":"The Westfield team''s #1 pigment corrector. Discoloration Defense + mineral SPF + periodic IPL is our gold-standard melasma protocol for Hamilton County patients who are serious about evening their tone.","carmel":"Our Carmel clinicians pair Discoloration Defense PM with Colorescience Even Up AM for around-the-clock pigment management. It''s the combination that finally moves the needle on stubborn dark spots and melasma."}'::JSONB,
  related_services = ARRAY['ipl-photofacial', 'chemical-peels', 'laser-resurfacing']
WHERE slug = 'discoloration-defense';

