-- 2. P Serum + Azelaic Acid (AZA)
UPDATE products SET
  image_url = '/images/products/universkin/p-serum.png',
  price = 165.00,
  size = '30ml / 1 fl oz',
  description = 'P Serum + Azelaic Acid (AZA) is a personalized serum by Universkin featuring provider-selected azelaic acid concentration for targeted treatment of redness, rosacea, congestion, and post-inflammatory pigmentation. Azelaic acid is one of the few active ingredients with proven efficacy across multiple skin concerns—it reduces inflammation, kills acne-causing bacteria, inhibits melanin production, and normalizes keratinization. Available exclusively at RELUXE Med Spa in Westfield and Carmel, Indiana.

Azelaic acid is uniquely valuable because it addresses both rosacea and acne in a single ingredient—two conditions that often coexist and require careful management. Unlike harsh acne treatments that can trigger rosacea flares, azelaic acid calms inflammation while clearing pores. The Universkin platform allows your RELUXE provider to select the optimal concentration for your skin—higher percentages for stubborn acne and congestion, moderate concentrations for rosacea and sensitivity maintenance. This customization is especially important for Hamilton County patients dealing with Indiana''s seasonal triggers—humidity-driven breakouts in summer, cold-weather rosacea flares in winter.',
  faq = '[{"q":"Is azelaic acid effective for rosacea?","a":"Yes—azelaic acid is one of the few ingredients with clinical evidence for both rosacea and acne. It reduces redness, calms inflammation, and normalizes skin without the irritation that many other actives cause. Our RELUXE providers customize the concentration based on your rosacea severity."},{"q":"Can azelaic acid help with dark spots from acne?","a":"Absolutely. Azelaic acid inhibits melanin production, making it effective for post-inflammatory hyperpigmentation (the dark marks acne leaves behind). It''s one of the most useful dual-purpose ingredients for acne-prone skin with pigmentation concerns."},{"q":"What concentration of azelaic acid will my serum contain?","a":"Your RELUXE provider determines the optimal concentration based on your skin analysis. Universkin offers a range of concentrations that can be adjusted over time as your skin responds and improves."},{"q":"Where can I get rosacea treatment near me in Westfield or Carmel?","a":"RELUXE Med Spa offers comprehensive rosacea management at both Hamilton County locations. Universkin P Serum + Azelaic Acid is part of our at-home rosacea protocol, paired with Colorescience All Calm SPF and in-clinic BBL or vascular laser treatments."}]'::JSONB,
  staff_picks = '{"westfield":"Our Westfield team''s Universkin pick for rosacea and breakout-prone skin. Azelaic acid calms and clears simultaneously—critical for Indiana patients whose skin reacts to seasonal humidity and temperature swings.","carmel":"The Carmel team''s go-to active for patients with redness + acne overlap. Custom-concentration azelaic acid addresses both concerns without triggering flares—something off-the-shelf products can''t do."}'::JSONB,
  related_services = ARRAY['acne-treatment', 'skin-consultation']
WHERE slug = 'p-serum-azelaic-acid';

-- 3. P Serum + Retinol (RET)
UPDATE products SET
  image_url = '/images/products/universkin/p-serum.png',
  price = 165.00,
  size = '30ml / 1 fl oz',
  description = 'P Serum + Retinol (RET) is a personalized serum by Universkin that delivers retinol at a provider-selected concentration tailored to your skin''s tolerance and anti-aging goals. Retinol remains the single most evidence-backed anti-aging ingredient in dermatology—stimulating collagen production, accelerating cell turnover, smoothing fine lines, and refining texture. The Universkin advantage is precision: your RELUXE provider starts you at exactly the right strength and can adjust upward as your skin builds tolerance, avoiding the irritation and peeling that come with one-size-fits-all retinol products. Available exclusively at RELUXE Med Spa in Westfield and Carmel, Indiana.

The biggest reason patients abandon retinol is irritation—and the biggest cause of irritation is starting too strong. Universkin solves this by allowing your provider to prescribe the exact concentration your skin can handle today, then incrementally increase it over time as tolerance builds. This personalized approach means you get retinol''s full anti-aging power without the redness, flaking, and discomfort that derail most people''s retinol journey. For patients who want the most potent retinoid available, your provider can also combine retinol with supporting ingredients like niacinamide (barrier support) or peptides (collagen boost) in the same serum—creating a multi-active formula that no off-the-shelf product can match.',
  faq = '[{"q":"What retinol strength will I start with?","a":"Your RELUXE provider determines the optimal starting concentration based on your skin type, sensitivity level, and prior retinol experience. Most patients start at a moderate concentration and increase gradually over 2-3 months."},{"q":"Is Universkin retinol better than over-the-counter retinol?","a":"The customization is the advantage. Over-the-counter products offer fixed concentrations—too weak for some, too strong for others. Universkin retinol is prescribed at exactly the right strength for your skin and can be adjusted as your tolerance improves."},{"q":"Can I combine retinol with other actives in my Universkin serum?","a":"Yes—that''s one of Universkin''s greatest strengths. Your provider can blend retinol with niacinamide, peptides, or other supporting ingredients in the same serum, creating a multi-active formula tailored to your specific skin goals."},{"q":"Where can I get professional retinol treatment in Hamilton County?","a":"RELUXE Med Spa in Westfield and Carmel offers personalized Universkin retinol protocols. Your provider will assess your skin, select the right starting concentration, and adjust over time for optimal results with minimal irritation."}]'::JSONB,
  staff_picks = '{"westfield":"Our Westfield team''s approach to retinol: start at exactly the right strength and scale up. Universkin retinol avoids the irritation that derails most patients across Hamilton County—because the concentration is prescribed, not guessed.","carmel":"The Carmel team''s personalized retinol for patients who want anti-aging results without the redness and peeling. Combined with niacinamide in the same serum, it''s the most tolerable retinol protocol available."}'::JSONB,
  related_services = ARRAY['microneedling', 'skin-consultation', 'botox']
WHERE slug = 'p-serum-retinol';

-- 4. P Serum + Tranexamic Acid (TA)
UPDATE products SET
  image_url = '/images/products/universkin/p-serum.png',
  price = 165.00,
  size = '30ml / 1 fl oz',
  description = 'P Serum + Tranexamic Acid (TA) is a personalized serum by Universkin that targets melasma and stubborn hyperpigmentation with provider-selected tranexamic acid concentration. Tranexamic acid works differently from traditional brightening agents—it interrupts the UV-triggered signaling pathway that tells melanocytes to produce excess pigment, addressing the root cause of hormonal and sun-induced discoloration rather than just bleaching the surface. Available exclusively at RELUXE Med Spa in Westfield and Carmel, Indiana.

Melasma is one of the most challenging skin conditions to manage because it''s driven by hormones, UV exposure, and heat—factors that are difficult to eliminate entirely. Indiana''s strong summer sun and outdoor lifestyle make melasma particularly persistent for Hamilton County residents. Tranexamic acid has emerged as one of the most effective ingredients for melasma maintenance because it works upstream in the pigmentation pathway, reducing the inflammatory signals that trigger melanin overproduction. Your RELUXE provider can customize the tranexamic acid concentration in your Universkin serum and combine it with other pigment-fighting actives like kojic acid or niacinamide for a multi-pathway approach. This personalized protocol, paired with daily mineral SPF and periodic in-clinic treatments, represents the most comprehensive melasma management available.',
  faq = '[{"q":"How does tranexamic acid treat melasma differently?","a":"Most brightening ingredients work by inhibiting tyrosinase (the enzyme that makes melanin). Tranexamic acid works upstream—it blocks the UV-triggered signals that tell melanocytes to overproduce melanin in the first place. This addresses the root cause of melasma rather than just the symptom."},{"q":"Can I combine tranexamic acid with other pigment correctors?","a":"Yes—your Universkin serum can combine tranexamic acid with kojic acid, niacinamide, or other brightening actives in a single formula. This multi-pathway approach is significantly more effective than any single ingredient alone."},{"q":"How long until I see improvement in my melasma?","a":"Most patients notice visible improvement in overall brightness within 4-6 weeks. Significant reduction in melasma patches typically occurs at 8-12 weeks with consistent daily use plus mineral SPF compliance."},{"q":"Where can I get melasma treatment near me in Indiana?","a":"RELUXE Med Spa offers comprehensive melasma management at both our Westfield and Carmel locations. Your personalized protocol may include Universkin tranexamic acid serum, SkinCeuticals Discoloration Defense, Colorescience Even Up SPF, and in-clinic treatments like IPL or chemical peels."}]'::JSONB,
  staff_picks = '{"westfield":"Our Westfield team''s top pick for melasma patients. Personalized tranexamic acid concentration + daily mineral SPF + periodic IPL at RELUXE is the most complete pigment protocol available in Hamilton County.","carmel":"The Carmel team combines Universkin TA with SkinCeuticals Discoloration Defense for multi-pathway pigment correction. Customized concentration means we can be more aggressive or gentler based on each patient''s skin."}'::JSONB,
  related_services = ARRAY['ipl-photofacial', 'chemical-peels', 'skin-consultation']
WHERE slug = 'p-serum-tranexamic-acid';

-- 5. P Serum + Kojic Acid (KOJ)
UPDATE products SET
  image_url = '/images/products/universkin/p-serum.png',
  price = 165.00,
  size = '30ml / 1 fl oz',
  description = 'P Serum + Kojic Acid (KOJ) is a personalized serum by Universkin that targets stubborn dark spots, sun damage, and post-inflammatory hyperpigmentation with provider-selected kojic acid concentration. Kojic acid is a powerful tyrosinase inhibitor—it blocks the enzyme responsible for melanin production, making it one of the most effective non-hydroquinone brightening agents available. Available exclusively at RELUXE Med Spa in Westfield and Carmel, Indiana.

Dark spots from sun damage, acne scars, and hormonal changes are among the most common complaints our Hamilton County patients bring to RELUXE. Kojic acid provides targeted, measurable lightening of these discolorations without the risks associated with hydroquinone (which can cause paradoxical darkening with long-term use). Your RELUXE provider selects the optimal concentration based on your pigmentation severity and skin sensitivity. For maximum results, kojic acid is often combined with tranexamic acid in the same Universkin serum—creating a dual-pathway formula that addresses pigmentation from two different angles simultaneously.',
  faq = '[{"q":"Is kojic acid safe for long-term use?","a":"Yes—unlike hydroquinone, which should only be used in cycles, kojic acid can be used continuously without risk of paradoxical darkening. Your Universkin concentration can be adjusted over time as your pigmentation improves."},{"q":"What types of dark spots does kojic acid treat?","a":"Kojic acid is effective against sun damage spots, post-inflammatory hyperpigmentation (acne scars), age spots, and melasma patches. It works by inhibiting the tyrosinase enzyme that drives melanin production."},{"q":"Can I combine kojic acid with tranexamic acid?","a":"Yes—this is one of the most effective Universkin combinations for stubborn pigmentation. Kojic acid blocks melanin production while tranexamic acid blocks the signals that trigger it. Together they attack pigmentation from two pathways for accelerated results."},{"q":"Where can I get dark spot treatment near me in Hamilton County?","a":"RELUXE Med Spa in Westfield and Carmel offers personalized pigment correction protocols using Universkin custom serums, SkinCeuticals Discoloration Defense, and in-clinic treatments like IPL and chemical peels."}]'::JSONB,
  staff_picks = '{"westfield":"Our Westfield team combines kojic acid with tranexamic acid in a single Universkin serum for the most stubborn pigmentation cases across Hamilton County. Dual-pathway correction that off-the-shelf products can''t match.","carmel":"The Carmel team''s targeted spot treatment. Custom kojic acid concentration means we can be precise—more aggressive on deep sun damage, gentler on post-acne marks—all in one personalized formula."}'::JSONB,
  related_services = ARRAY['ipl-photofacial', 'chemical-peels', 'skin-consultation']
WHERE slug = 'p-serum-kojic-acid';

